@startuml 18_Domain_Expert_Agents
!theme plain
title DRE 3D Framework -- D3 Domain Expert Agents\n12 Agents . 5 Domain Categories . Auto-Fix with Human-in-Loop Review

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #546E7A
  ActorBorderColor #263238
  LifeLineBorderColor #B0BEC5
  ParticipantBorderColor #90A4AE
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BoxBorderColor #CFD8DC
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF8E1
  BorderColor #FFB300
  FontColor #4E342E
  FontSize 10
}

participant "D3 Approval Gate\n(human sign-off)" as Gate
participant "Domain Router\n(selects agent\nby domain tag)" as Router
participant "Domain Expert Agent\n(selected instance)" as Agent
participant "Data Pipeline\n(upstream job\nor transform)" as Pipeline
database "Target Domain Table\n(Delta Lake)"          as Table
participant "D1 ANOMALY_DETECTION_JOB\n(re-validation)" as D1
database "DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\n(Delta)"            as ADB
database "table_daily_metrics\n(Delta)"               as MDB
participant "Notification Service\n(Email / Jira)"       as Notify

note right of Gate
  12 Domain Expert Agents (source: DRE.pptx slide 6):
  Consumer Engagement : adiClub, CRM, Consumer Service, NPS
  Marketing & Traffic : Clickstream, Affiliate, Paid Search, SEO
  Sales               : DTC Sales
  Payments            : Payments
  Metadata            : Metadata Agent
  Trading             : Trading Agent
  All agents share the same 4-step execution protocol.
  Each agent owns its domain fix logic + pipeline knowledge.
end note

== [1] Prescription Routing (D3 handover) ==

Gate -> Router : Approved prescription token\n{domain_tag, table, fix_steps[],\n severity, blast_radius, owner, jira_id}
activate Router

note right of Router
  Domain tag -> Agent mapping:
  consumer_engagement -> adiClub / CRM / Consumer Service / NPS
  marketing_traffic   -> Clickstream / Affiliate / Paid Search / SEO
  sales               -> DTC Sales Agent
  payments            -> Payments Data Agent
  metadata            -> Metadata Agent
  trading             -> Trading Agent
end note

Router -> Agent : Dispatch to matched domain agent\n{fix_steps[], target_table,\n domain_context, owner}
activate Agent

== [2] Step 1 -- Auto-Fix with Human Review Gate ==

Agent -> Table : Apply fix per prescription.steps[]\n(UPDATE / DELETE / BACKFILL / REPROCESS\nas defined by Playbook Compiler JSON recipe)
activate Table
Table --> Agent : {rows_affected, fix_ts, table_version}
deactivate Table

Agent -> Notify : Human review request\n{fix_applied, rows_affected,\n sample_preview[], owner, jira_id}
activate Notify
Notify --> Agent : APPROVED\n(owner click-to-approve via Jira / Email)
deactivate Notify

== [3] Step 2 -- Pipeline Enhancement (prevent recurrence) ==

Agent -> Pipeline : Patch upstream job or transform logic\n(e.g. add null guard, fix partition filter,\n correct join key, fix SLA window)
activate Pipeline
Pipeline --> Agent : {patch_id, job_version, config_updated}
deactivate Pipeline

== [4] Step 3 -- End-to-End Testing ==

Agent -> D1 : Re-run original failing DQ assertion\n(trigger targeted ANOMALY_DETECTION_JOB\nfor this config_id only)
activate D1
D1 -> Table : Execute DQ check (SELECT-only)
Table --> D1 : {result: PASS|FAIL, violation_rate}
D1 --> Agent : {validation_result, check_execution_log_id}
deactivate D1

alt Validation FAIL -- fix did not fully resolve issue
  Agent -> Notify : Escalate: auto-fix insufficient\n(owner + Tech Lead alerted)
  Agent -> Router : Return to D2 for deeper root-cause\n(re-enter Segment Slicer / Playbook Compiler)
else Validation PASS -- fix confirmed
  Agent -> ADB : UPDATE DIGITAL_DATA_ANOMALIES\nSET diagnosis_status = 'RESOLVED'\n    fix_applied      = fix_description\n    resolved_at      = NOW()\n    resolved_by_agent = domain_agent_name\nWHERE anomaly_id = ?
  Agent -> MDB : UPSERT table_daily_metrics\n(refresh EWMA baseline post-fix\nso next D1 run uses corrected reference point)
end

== [5] Step 4 -- Production Release Plan ==

Agent -> Notify : Release notification\n{fix_summary, validation_evidence,\n pipeline_patch_id, prod_promotion_ts,\n jira_closure, owner_sign_off}
activate Notify
Notify --> Agent : {Email delivered, Jira ticket CLOSED}
deactivate Notify

Agent --> Router : Execution report\n{status: RESOLVED|ESCALATED,\n fix_id, domain, duration_sec,\n rows_repaired, pipeline_patched}
deactivate Agent

Router --> Gate : Domain agent complete\n{domain, agent_used, outcome, jira_id}
deactivate Router

@enduml
